Package au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.collections

Class DynamicList<T>

java.lang.Object
au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.collections.DynamicList<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of the list items
All Implemented Interfaces:
Sizeable, Textable, Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, Deque<T>, List<T>, Queue<T>
public class DynamicList<T> extends Object implements List<T>, Deque<T>, Queue<T>, Sizeable, Textable
Implementation of List<T> with a self-correcting iterator which allows removing of items while in a for loop on the list. It is implemented as a linked list with a clever iterator that skips removed items while looping. Use this class when dealing with highly dynamic lists (where there are many insertions and deletions in the list).

[NB:This was formerly known as AotList. Code modified from au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.collections. AotList<T> by Shayne Flint. Removed Query, and dependency from AotCollection and AotIterable.]

Given the new facilities provided in java 8 lists, this class may be obsolete. For example, to remove items from a list can be done with instructions such as list.sublist(from,to).clear().

Author:
Shayne Flint - loooong ago.
refactored by Jacques Gignoux - 30 Nov. 2018
